{
  "stem": "10699.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we were-- we had friends who were foreign Jews and were hidden.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we knew exactly what was happening, that they were being taken.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "What we never knew exactly-- and I must admit it-- is that we knew that the Jews were being sent to camps, you know, we thought to working camps.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Although the-- somehow the world knew that in '42, there were already concentration camps, I don't know if we didn't-- why we didn't know that there were concentration camps or death camps.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We did not know.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My family didn't know and their friends didn't know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They lived in fear.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They knew that people who were sent away hadn't come back.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But they didn't know that there were death camps.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "This we really were not in the know-how and ignorant about it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We knew about Dachau-- all these camps that the Germans opened already for their own people and for-- and for-- in Germany, where they sent all the unwanted ones they'd already they sent to Dachau and the terrible things they do to their own people that were against regime.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We followed all of that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But-- and we, we also heard about the terrible things that were happening in, in occupied France, you know, because people smuggled through in, in the locomotives in the-- under the coals, you know, were hidden there with families, and came through to the demarcation line, you know, that that-- we heard all those horrible stories, that husbands were taken away and shot, that Resistance were taken and, and, and, and were caught.",
      "word_count": 73
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Because my brother wanted to go in the Resistance.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And my mother wouldn't let him.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I don't know if she was right or not.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But she couldn't cope with it.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
